.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
Wrapper around the stack levels - keeps a pointer to the current top and bottom of the stack and a count of the current height\&. This allows the top to have non-null above pointer resulting from previously allocated stack levels that may be recycled later without \fRmalloc\fP overhead\&. 
.SH "Field Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "\fBstack_lvl_t\fP* bottom"
The bottom of the stack\&. If this is NULL, the stack is empty\&. 
.SS "int height"
The current height of the stack, in terms of allocated and used levels\&. 
.SS "\fBstack_lvl_t\fP* top"
The top of the stack\&. If this is NULL, the stack is empty\&. 

